		<div id="comment_body_64566377"><p><span class="substr"> </span> <em> Is executing a field that changes and in which you need to constantly be learning new things?</em> </p><p>Yes.  It's one of the pillars <a href="https://247wallst.com/banking-finance-and-taxes/2024/05/26/10-life-lessons-from-warren-buffett-every-person-in-their-50s-should-hear/" title="247wallst.com">Warren Buffett relies on</a> [247wallst.com] (item 2).  If, as an executive, you're not trying to figure out how AI may or may not affect your business, what its cost may or may not be, what new processes are coming along that might enhance or detract from your business, you're not doing your job. Does this mean you need to know everything about everything? Of course not.  But you better be willing and ab</p></div>
